k tidal interactions likely playing\nimportant roles in the evolution of disk material. From the perspective of the\nmass content of the disk, we expect that (giant) planet formation is inhibited\naround the components of close pairs or secondaries, but should be as likely as\nfor single stars around the primaries (or wide tertiaries in hierarchical\ntriples) in more widely-separated multiple star systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 Mar 2012 20:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
